Package com.avanza.astrix.provider.core

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    AstrixApiProvider
    Used to identify an ApiProvider.
    AstrixApplication
    Used to define what services a given Astrix server provides.
    AstrixConfigDiscovery
    Annotating a service bean definition with this annotation indicates that providers of the given service should be discovered using the configuration rather than the default behavior of using the service registry.
    AstrixDynamicQualifier  
    AstrixExcludedByProfile
    Annotating an AstrixApiProvider with this annotation indicates that it should be excluded when a given profile is active.
    AstrixIncludedByProfile
    Annotating an AstrixApiProvider with this annotation indicates that it should only be used when the corresponding profile is active.
    AstrixQualifier
    Annotations used to qualify an Astrix-bean.
    AstrixServiceExport  
    AstrixServiceRegistryDiscovery
    Used to indicate that services should be located using the service registry
    DefaultBeanSettings
    Allows Overriding the default bean settings for a given Astrix bean by annotating the exported bean type.
    Library
    Used to publish a library as part of an api, see AstrixApiProvider for more information.
    Service
    Used to publish a service as part of an api, see AstrixApiProvider for more information.
    ServiceConfig
    Allows additional configuration of AstrixServiceComponent's.
